🔥 1. Smokey Eyeshadow Description Formula

Use this structure:
[Mood] + [Color Palette] + [Texture/Finish] + [Occasion or Vibe]

Example Descriptions:
	1.	“Smolder in soft charcoal and deep plum with a satin finish — your go-to glam for sultry nights.”
	2.	“Mystery meets elegance: this classic black-and-silver smokey eye blends effortlessly for an after-dark statement.”
	3.	“From dusk to drama — rich espresso and bronze tones create the ultimate soft glam smokey eye.”
	4.	“Edgy yet effortless: matte charcoal melts into shimmer pewter for a rockstar-ready look.”
	5.	“A modern twist on the timeless smokey eye — think gunmetal shimmer, velvet blend, and fierce confidence.”

Use power words: sultry, bold, soft, glam, drama, smolder, melt, blend, fierce, velvet, shimmer,

Hosted by: IBS – International Beauty Studio

🖌️ 1. Introduction to Makeup Brushes
	•	Purpose: Enhance makeup application precision, hygiene, and finish.
	•	Types: Natural vs Synthetic bristles
	•	Natural: Made from animal hair, best for powder products.
	•	Synthetic: Man-made fibers (nylon/taklon), ideal for liquids and creams.
Face brush Brush Type
Use
Tips
Foundation Brush
Liquid/cream foundation

Use light sweeping motions

Blush application
